snippet.textDisplay: School is the last place these kids should be. That's exactly where they're having this complete and utter bullshit rammed in to their heads. Yes climate change is happening but to suggest that the building block of all life on earth is the number 1 cause of it is a clear indication that you haven't reviewed the science. You don't understand it and you haven't used any sort of critical evaluation skills to try and understand what's really going on. No matter though because whether you believe carbon is causing climate change or it's an entirely natural process (which it is) the only real solution is the same. Armour the planet with green stuff, stop raping the water in the landscape and stop burning fossil fuels. Regenerative agriculture is the key to reversing the man made exacerbation of climate change and buffering the planet from its natural causes. Fortunately just as renewable energy is becoming more cost effective than fossil fuel, regenerative agriculture is becoming more cost effective than industrial agriculture. The necessary changes are inevitible and they are happening so if you want protection from the real effects of climate change put your consumer dollars behind real solutions or better yet make it your life's work. I'm happy to debate any alarmist or denier but make sure you bring the science you so arrogantly profess to "know" because I'll be bringing mine. Most of you will simply have dropped out by now though. This is clearly tldr
